.TH "rt_mutex_timed_lock" 9 "rt_mutex_timed_lock" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
rt_mutex_timed_lock \- lock a rt_mutex interruptible the timeout structure is provided by the caller
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" rt_mutex_timed_lock
.BI "(struct rt_mutex *lock "  ","
.BI "struct hrtimer_sleeper *timeout "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "lock" 12
the rt_mutex to be locked
.IP "timeout" 12
timeout structure or NULL (no timeout)
.SH "RETURN"
0           on success
-EINTR       when interrupted by a signal
-ETIMEDOUT   when the timeout expired
